# Walkthrough: Phase 8 Integrated (Traveler Movement Context)

Phase 8 is now fully operational, bringing on-demand station-level visibility to the ICS Border Control System. We've enhanced both the analytical depth and situational awareness of the platform.

## Key Accomplishments

### 📊 Tactical Command Dashboard
- **24-Hour Situational Awareness**: Re-calibrated the main crossing volume chart to a rolling 24-hour window for comprehensive oversight.
- **Operational Distribution**: Added a new **Station Activity** chart (Last 24h) to identify the busiest border ports at a glance.
- **Integrity Metrics**: Integrated real-time performance telemetry including biometric verification rates and processing speeds.

### 🕵️ Forensic Intelligence & Profiling
- **Primary Port Identification**: The Traveler Profile now automatically calculates and highlights the **Primary Port** (most frequent crossing point) for every individual.
- **Mobility Anomaly Detection**: The Risk Assessment engine now flags "Anomalous Mobility" if a traveler crosses through more than 3 distinct border stations, aiding in the detection of irregular movement patterns.

### 📑 Industrial Reporting Hub
- **Station Audit**: The Crossing Audit report now features a multi-dimensional "Intelligence" view, showcasing station distribution alongside historical volume trends.
- **Flexible Data Entry**: Maintained industrial flexibility by allowing free-text "Point of Entry" while providing a curated dropdown for common stations.

## Database & Schema Upgrades
- **Schema Hardening**: Updated the `nationality` constraints to support international standards (increased to 50 characters).
- **Data Fidelity**: Re-seeded the national database with diverse movement records across *Addis Ababa (Bole)*, *Moyale*, *Togochale*, and *Galafi* to populate the new dashboards.

## Verification Success
- [x] **Schema Migration**: Success (Phase 8 column added, nationality lengthened).
- [x] **Data Seeding**: Success (8 diverse crossing records across multiple stations).
- [x] **API Integrity**: Success (Station stats correctly aggregated in `/api/reports/stats`).
- [x] **UI Rendering**: Success (All new charts and indicators visible).

> [!TIP]
> Navigating to **Mission Reporting Hub** -> **Daily Crossing Audit** -> **Intelligence** will now display the national station distribution for any selected time period.
